<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at GMT 1600, September 28 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL -- Ten people were killed and seven others seriously
wounded on Monday when a coach traveling along the Seoul-Pusan
highway crashed down into a field in North Kyongsang, South Korea.
</P>
<P>
The coach broke a guardrail and careened into the farmland five
meter below the highway while trying to negotiate a curb on the
Seoul-Pusan highway. (SKorea-Accident)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Shots were fired on Monday at a group of Israeli
students in the West Bank city of Hebron, injuring one girl
student, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli students were headed toward the Jewish enclave of
Tel Rumeida in the center of the city when shots were fired at
them from the Palestinian-controlled part of the city and the
female student was wounded in the leg, the Radio
said. (Israel-Hebron Shooting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
COLOMBO -- At least 194 Tamil rebels and 43 soldiers were
killed in a fierce battle between government troops and the Tamil
rebels in the Northern Province of Sri Lanka Sunday, according to
a news release issued Monday.
</P>
<P>
The release from the Defense Ministry said at least 194 of the
rebel cadres were killed and a large number of rebels wounded in
the confrontation which took place south of Paranthan in
Kilinochchi.
</P>
<P>
A total of 43 government troops were killed and 110 others
wounded during the battle, the release said. (SriLanka-Battle)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOGADISHU -- The security situation in Mogadishu and its
surrounding areas is worsening as a new wave of killing, robbing,
looting and kidnaping began in recent days, despite efforts to
restore law and order in the Somali capital.
</P>
<P>
At least five people were killed and more than seven others
were wounded in separate armed clashes in Mogadishu Sunday
afternoon. (Somalia-Mogadishu-Situation) 
</P>
</TEXT>
