<HEADLINE> Simitis Congratulates German Chancellor-Elect Schroeder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Greek Prime Minister Costas
Simitis Monday called German chancellor-elect Gerhard Schroeder to
congratulate him on winning Germany's elections.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing, Greek government spokesman
Dimitris Reppas said that both Simitis and Schroeder agreed to
meet at the earliest convenient date.
</P>
<P>
Simitis also sent Schroeder a congratulatory telegram, hoping
that the two governments could work together on social policy in
Europe to fight against unemployment and in laying the foundations
for a European common foreign policy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Reppas said that Germany's foreign policy would continue to
contribute to the European Union's progress and to the creation of
conditions for cooperation in Europe as a whole.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also praised the outgoing chancellor, Helmut Kohl
for his contributions to the unity of his nation, saying that Kohl
was definitive for Germany's reunification and for the efforts to
unify Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
