<HEADLINE> One Drowned, 18 Missing in Boat Accident in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 28 (Xinhua) -- One person was drowned and
18 others went missing Sunday when a rafting boat capsized at the
confluence of two rivers in Sindhupalchok district of central
Nepal, the Kantipur daily reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Another 17 people managed to swim to the bank and survived, the
Nepalese-language newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
They were on their way home from a local market when the
tragedy happened, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Nepalese are now celebrating Dashain, the biggest festival
in the country. 
</P>
