<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hans Von Sponeck Appointed Humanitarian Coordinator  in Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 28 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan on Monday appointed Hans Von Sponeck of Germany as
United Nations Humanitarian Coordinator in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Von Sponeck will succeed Mr. Denis Halliday who leaves Iraq
on September 30.
</P>
<P>
As Humanitarian coordinator, at Assistance Secretary-General
level, Mr. Von Sponeck will report to the Executive Director of
the Office of the Iraq Program, Benon Sevan.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Secretary-General established the Office of the Iraq
Program in October 1997 to consolidate the management of United
Nations Secretariat activities related to Security Council
resolutions 986 of 1995 and 661 of 1990.
</P>
<P>
Since the first deliveries in 1997, nearly seven million tons
of food worth more than 2.2 billion U.S. dollars and 366 million
U.S. dollars worth of medicine have been delivered to Iraq under
the oil-for-food program.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Von Sponeck has degrees from the University of Tubingen and
the University of Bonn in modern European history and from the
Louisiana States university and Washington State University in
anthropology and sociology.
</P>
<P>
He will leave his current post as Regional Representative and
Director of European Affairs at the United Nations Development
Program's Office in Geneva and take up new duties in Baghdad
towards the end of October.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
