<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Meets With Iraq's Tareq Aziz </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 28 (xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan on Monday met with Iraq's Deputy Prime Minister Tareq
Aziz.
</P>
<P>
During the one-hour meeting, Annan and Aziz discussed the
recent seven-week long standoff between the U.N. weapons
inspectors and Iraq and the U.N. Chief's proposal to break the
impasse.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also discussed Annan's ideas for a comprehensive
review of Iraq's compliance with U.N. resolutions which requested
Iraq destroy all its weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
Aziz, who came to the headquarters of the United Nations in New
York at the invitation of the U.N. Secretary_General, leads a team
that include Iraq's Foreign Minister Said al-Sahaf, Oil Minister
Amer Mohammed and Deputy Foreign Minister Riyadh al-Qaisi as well
as a top adviser to President Saddam Hussein.
</P>
<P>
Aziz is expected to stay here for a couple of days during which
he is due to meet other members of the Security Council of the
United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Iraq suspended its cooperation with the United Nations Special
Commission (UNSCOM) in charge of dismantling Iraq's weapons of
mass destruction on August 3 when the talks between Iraq and
UNSCOM collapsed due to the sharp differences between them.
</P>
</TEXT>
