<DOCNO> XIE19980929.0021 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Library Network Broadens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The number of the
United Nations depository libraries rose to 365 with the latest
designation of South Korea's Pusan National University Library,
the U.N. Department of Public Information said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Among the libraries, 53 are located in Africa, 99 in Asia and
Pacific, 30 in Eastern Europe, 84 in Western Europe, 46 in latin
America and 53 in North America.
</P>
<P>
The libraries receive U.N. materials, keep them in good order
and provide them to the public free of charge.
</P>
<P>
Each of the 185 U.N. member states is entitled to one "free
depository", usually the national library in the capital city,
with other depository libraries paying token annual contribution
to receive U.N documentation.
</P>
<P>
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan has paid great importance to
the U.N. library system, hoping that it will help promote U.N.
causes of peace and development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
