<HEADLINE> Cape Verde PM Wounded in Plane Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Cape Verde Prime Minister
Carlos Veiga was wounded Monday in a plane accident, reports from
Praia said.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when the plane, a twinotter, was landing
at the Praia Airport.
</P>
<P>
Angola News Agency Monday quoted Simao Monteiro, Justice
Minister of Cape Verde, as saying that one of Veiga's bodyguards
was dead and his other company were wounded.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the prime minister's life was not
endangered. He is now receiving treatment in a hospital in the
capital city.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is not immediately clear. But some
sources said there was a big wind when the accident happened and
the visibility at the airport was low. 
</P>
