<HEADLINE> Congo (k) Rebels Seek Aid to Relocate Ethnic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, Septmber 28 (Xinhua)-- The rebels fighting to
overthrow President Laurent Kabila of the Democratic Republic of
Congo (DRC) are seeking for international aid to relocate about
20,000 ethnic Tutsi--Banyamulenge fleeing alleged massacres,
the rebel-held Radio Bukavu reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Governor of south Kivu, Benjamin Serukiza was quoted as
saying that the Banyamulenge were displaced by the massacres
orchestrated by troops loyalist to Kabila in Kalemie and Moba
districts in Katanga Province.
</P>
<P>
The radio announced that they will be shifted together with
their cattle heads to the Ruzizi Valley in south Kivu where the
security will be better than in Katanga.
</P>
<P>
Some Western countries like Belgium, France, the United
States, the Britain, as well as some international humanitarian
agences like the United Nations High Commission for Refugees, the
International Committee for the Red Cross are expected to assist
in this operation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a rebel delegation led by led by Earnest Wamba dia
Wamba and former Congolese foreign minister, Bizima Karaha, went
at the weekend to Zambia for talks with officials from the
Southern African development Community officials.  
</P>
