<HEADLINE> Mozambican National Park to Be Re-Opened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The Gorongosa National Park
in central Mozambique's Sofala Province will be re-opened to the
public on October 1 after over 10 years of interval, the
Mozambique News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Roberto Zolho, manager of the park, said the Chitenge airport
near the park has been repaired with 1,200-meter-long runway for
small and medium sized planes.
</P>
<P>
Gorongosa National Park is a well-known scenic spot in
Mozambique, with many varieties of wild animals. Before the
country's independence in 1975, the park had drawn a large number
of tourists from South Africa and Europe.
</P>
<P>
During the 16-year civil war, the park had been turned into the
base for opposition National Resistance of Mozambique (Renamo).
</P>
<P>
Since peace was finally achieved in the country in 1992, the
government has invested a lot in de-mining and repairing
infrastructure damaged by the war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
