<HEADLINE> Clinton: Progress Made, More Work Needed for Mideast Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 28 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill
Clinton, after meeting leaders of Israeli and Palestinian leaders,
said that progress has been made but there are still a lot of work
to do before reaching an agreement.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that we all agree that we have made progress on the
path to peace," Clinton said during a photo opportunity with
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
"There has been a significant narrowing of the gaps between the
two parties across a wide range of issues that were in the
American initiative we've been working on for months," Clinton
said.
</P>
<P>
However, Clinton noted that "there is still a substantial
amount of work to be done until a comprehensive agreement can be
reached."
</P>
