praised the outgoing chancellor Helmut Kohl for his contribution
to the unity of his nation as well as to the strengthening of
German-Romanian bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The outcome of German elections evoked reactions among Romanian
political leaders.
</P>
<P>
"I hope the Romanian-German relations will not be influenced by
the German elections outcome. Foreign policy is a national one not
that of a single political party. I hope we will further enjoy
Germany's support for the Romanian economy's recovery,"
Ion Diaconescu, the Speaker of the Romanian Chamber of
Deputies and the leader of the ruling coalition's major party
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ion Iliescu, leader of the Party of Social Democracy, the
largest opposition, expressed the hope that the relations between
Romania and Germany will keep developing, after the new
Governement's coming to rule. 
</P>
