<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Inoculate Children Against Polio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique started Monday to
inoculate for the second time children under five years against
polio.
</P>
<P>
The objective set by the health authorities is to vaccine
about three million children by October 2.
</P>
<P>
Media reports here said 97 percent of children under five
around the country were vaccined during August 24 and 28.
</P>
<P>
Four cases of polio were reported in Mozambique last year, all
of which were discovered in the northern part of the country.
</P>
<P>
Health experts believe that there is still the danger of the
possible spread of the disease so long as there are virus
carriers in the country.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the government has mobilized the press and medical
personnel to ensure every child under five years of age is
inoculated against polio. 
</P>
