<HEADLINE> Greece Hopes Situation in Albania to Return to Normal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Greece hoped the situation in
neighboring Albania would soon return to normal, Greek government
spokesman Dimitris Reppas said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the resignation of Albanian Prime Minister Fatos
Nano, Reppas said that if democratic institutions were working,
the transfer of power from one person to another did not
constitute a dramatic development.
</P>
<P>
Greece's Defense Minister Akis Tsohatzopoulos also said Tuesday
that Albania was currently in the throes of a political crisis,
which could lead to new operational procedures of the neighboring
country that would disengage it from the policies of the past.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Greece could offer its undivided support for
stabilization of the political system if the democratic procedures
and political decisions were respected in Albania. 
