<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Likely to Receive More Aid From Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Japan is considering an
additional assistance of around 100 million U.S. dollars to
Bangladesh for flood relief and post-flood rehabilitation, the
official BSS news agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese Foreign Ministry indicated to Bangladeshi
Ambassador in Tokyo that Japan is considering this additional
assistance on the basis of recommendations of a Japanese
fact-finding team that recently visited Dhaka, BSS quoted a
message from the Bangladeshi Embassy in Tokyo as saying.
</P>
<P>
This would be in addition to the Japanese emergency
humanitarian assistance of 220,000 dollars which was provided
immediately after the devastating floods hit Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
Besides the additional assistance, Japan is also considering
extending yen loans for a Dhaka flood protection embankment
project upon receiving details of the project from the Bangladeshi
government.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese government is also considering building flood
shelters and would conduct further discussion and study on this
matter, the message said. It added that the additional package of
aid is expected to be announced soon. 
</P>
