<HEADLINE> Griffith Joyner to be Honored </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Florence Griffith
Joyner,the women's 100 and 200 meter world record holder who died
on September 21, will be honored on February 11 at the Jesse
Owens International Trophy Dinner.
</P>
<P>
Griffith Joyner, who died at age of 38 in her sleep at her
home last Monday, won the Jesse Owens award in 1989, a year after
setting both records - 10.49 seconds for the 100m and 21.34 for
the 200m at the 1988 Seoul Olympics, where she won three gold
medals.
</P>
<P>
Griffith Joyner's sudden death refueled rumors that her
record-beating performances were aided by banned drugs. The cause
of her death has not been determined. Her funeral was held last
weekend. 
</P>
