<HEADLINE> Shanghai Gold Store Presents Gold Book on Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 29 (Xinhua) -- A leading gold store in
Shanghai has "published" a book made of pure gold on late Chinese
leader Deng Xiaoping, a volume said to be the first of its kind in
China.
</P>
<P>
The book, titled "Deng Xiaoping -- A Great Man of the Century",
was created by the Shanghai Laofengxiang Gold Store, which has a
history of 150 years. The book includes a collection of 50
pictures depicting Deng's life.
</P>
<P>
The producers say they applied technologies such as high-energy
physics to turn the gold paper, which originally was fragile and
easily broken, into soft and pliable material, all the while
maintaining its high purity.
</P>
<P>
The book was sent for display at the Second China Gem and Jade
Fair which opened today in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is said to be China's largest market for the sale of
gold ornaments, and the volume of retail sales in the city's
jewelry and jadeware market totalled two billion yuan (about 250
million U.S. dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said the city hopes to establish itself as
one of the largest gem and jade markets in Asia by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
The Gem and Jade Fair is being held at the Shanghai No.1
Department Store, and will last six days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
