<HEADLINE> China Holds National Day Reception for Overseas Chinese (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,000 overseas
Chinese and compatriots from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan gathered
in the Great Hall of the People in Beijing this evening to
celebrate the 49th founding anniversary of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the reception, Qian Qichen, vice-premier of the
State Council, welcomed the compatriots and extended earnest
greetings and wishes to the overseas Chinese and compatriots in
Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Qian said China is enjoying increasing prestige worldwide with
the achievements scored in the reform and opening-up over the past
two decades.
</P>
<P>
Although China suffered from severe floods this year, the army
and the people made joint efforts to fight the floods, and won a
significant victory in the campaign, he said, noting that the
Chinese people are confident and able to overcome all difficulties
and build China into a strong, prosperous, democratic and
civilized country.
</P>
<P>
Qian also voiced thanks to overseas Chinese for their help in
the flood-relief work, and said the Chinese government will
continue to offer a good investment environment and improve
services for them.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980929.0067 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
