<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets Philippines Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), met here today with a delegation of overseas
Chinese and compatriots in the Philippines here to attend China's
National Day celebration.
</P>
<P>
Li, who is also a member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China, expressed his welcome to the visiting Filipino
delegation on behalf of the Chinese government and people, and
praised them for their contribution to Sino-Philippines friendship.
</P>
<P>
Li said the overseas Chinese and compatriots living abroad are
always concerned with the development of China and have made great
contributions to the reform and opening. He also expressed thanks
to the overseas Chinese for their generous donations to this
year's flood-relief efforts.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government and people care about and
support the development of overseas Chinese and wish them success
in all fields.
</P>
<P>
As guests of the Office of Overseas Chinese Affairs under the
State Council, the 104-member Filipino delegation came to Beijing
to attend celebrations for the 49th anniversary of the founding of
the People's Republic of China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
