<HEADLINE> Arab Media to Launch Jerusalem Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Arab media experts will meet
here on Wednesday to work out plans for helping protect Jerusalem
from Israel's judaization attempts, Egypt's Middle East News
Agency (MENA) reported.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the experts will draw up an action plan to
expose Israel's incessant attempts to alter Jerusalem demographic
landscape by demolishing Arab houses and evicting Arab
inhabitants, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian permanent representative to the Arab League
Mohamed Sobeih is due to submit a detailed report to the meeting
on the developments of the Jerusalem issue and the Arab, Muslim
and international efforts against the illegal Israeli measures.
</P>
<P>
Israeli government drew Muslim anger and a chorus of world
criticism early this year when it made public a scheme to expand
the boundaries of Jerusalem, which is holy to Muslims, Christians
and Jews.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians want the traditionally Arab East Jerusalem as
the capital of their future independent state while Israel claims
Jerusalem as its "undivided, eternal capital."
</P>
<P>
"The media plan also involves the publication of a series of
booklets entitled `Jerusalem Is of Arab Identity' in a number of
foreign languages, tracing the historical facts of the holy city,
and its Islamic and Christian landmarks," Sobeih said, quoted by
MENA.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that the United Arab Emirates has financed the
production of a film on Jerusalem, which will be broadcast on Arab
TV channels soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
