<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Urges Cross-Straits Political Dialogue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Qian
Qichen today voiced the hope that the Taiwan authorities will do
something practical to boost cross-straits exchanges and pave
the way for political dialogue between both sides across the
Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark at a reception held here today by the
Overseas Chinese Affairs Office, the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs
Office, and the Taiwan Affairs Office of the State Council to mark
the 49th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of
China.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese nation is now faced with the historical
mission to realize peaceful reunification between both sides of
the Taiwan Straits, with the return of Hong Kong and the
approaching return of Macao.
</P>
<P>
As concerted efforts of the people on both sides, cross-straits
personnel, economic and cultural exchanges have maintained steady
growth, Qian said, noting that the attempt to create "Taiwan
independence," "two Chinas" and "one China, one Taiwan" will be
firmly rejected.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that the central government will continue to
implement the principle of "peaceful reunification, and one
country, two systems" and the eight-point proposition for
peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
Cross-straits political dialogue has been put on the agenda,
and the interests of the Taiwan compatriots will be entirely
protected under the "one country, two systems" concept, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qian pointed out that the love of Taiwan and the love of the
motherland by the Taiwan compatriots are in complete accord with
each other.
</P>
<P>
"We will, as always, go together with Taiwan compatriots, Hong
Kong and Macao compatriots and overseas Chinese, and jointly
strive for the great cause of peaceful reunification of the
motherland," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
