<HEADLINE> S.Korea, Australia to Further Expand Trade Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 29 (Xinhua) -- South Korea and Australia
agreed Tuesday to expand the annual bilateral trade volume to 10
billion U.S. dollars by the year 2000 from last year's eight
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached at the 20th annual meeting of the
South Korea-Australia Business Council, which opened here Tuesday
with the participation of 70 South Korean and 36 Australian
businessmen.
</P>
<P>
The two nations agreed to establish a bilateral subcommittee on
trade under the council.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, South Korea asked the Australian government to
double the trade financing for South Korea's raw-material
importers from one billion Australian dollars to two billion.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Australia will boost investment in South Korea if
the nation's restructuring reforms and privatization of public
corporations make further progress.
</P>
<P>
Australia is the thirteenth largest exporter to South Korea.
</P>
