<HEADLINE> DPR Korea to Meet China in Women's Team Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 29 (Xinhua) -- World runners-up DPR Korea
edged Hong Kong of China 3-2 in a semifinal on Tuesday to meet
world champions China in the women's team final at the Asian
Table Tennis Championships in Osaka, Japan.
</P>
<P>
The DPR Korea team, led by Kim Hyon-Hui, battled more than
three hours to beat the Hong Kong team, establishing another
clash against China since their loss at the world championships
in Manchester in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The DPR Korea paddlers seemed to have a setback when Wi
Bok-Sun lost to Hong Kong's Wong Ching 14-21, 17-21 in the opener
but Kim managed to level the score by beating Chan Tan-Lui 21-15,
19-21, 23-21.
</P>
<P>
DPR Korea's Tu Jong-Sil defeated Song Ah-sim 21-9, 21-13 but
Wi then lost to Chan 19-21, 19-21.
</P>
<P>
In the decider, Kim anchored the victory for DPR Korea by
beating Wong 21-17, 13-21, 21-7.
</P>
<P>
In the other semifinal, China whitewashed South Korea 3-0.
</P>
<P>
World number two Li Ju beat Kim Moo-Kyo 21-8, 21-19, Wang Nan
defeated Ryu Ji-Hye 21-12, 21-10 while Zhang Yining defeated Lee
Eun-Sil 21-18, 21-15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
