<HEADLINE> Largest Coal Mining, Shipping Enterprises Set Up Joint Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 29 (Xinhua) -- China's largest coal mining
enterprise and its giant ocean-going shipping line today jointly
established the Yuanhua Shipping Company in the seaport city of
Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The Shenhua Group, engaged in coal mining, railway
transportation, and power plant and port construction, has annual
coal exports of over one-million tons and is expected to reach
about four-million tons by the start of the next century.
</P>
<P>
China Ocean Shipping Corporation (COSCO) has the world's
largest fleet of bulk freighters with 108, and a total deadweight
capacity of over 5.7-million tons.
</P>
<P>
The newly created shipping company will link the coal fields of
Shenfu and Dongsheng to the overseas markets, according to company
officials.  
</P>
