<HEADLINE> 2 Killed, 14 Injured in Greece Road Accidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and 14
injured in a series of traffic accidents in the Greek capital of
Athens on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
There were 75 road accidents Tuesday morning, including a
15-car pile-up on Kifissias Avenue, a main thoroughfare in the
capital, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police attributed the traffic accidents to sudden rainstorms.
</P>
<P>
Greek Prime Minister Costas Simitis chaired on Tuesday a
special meeting to discuss with ministers the ways to handle
traffic problems.
</P>
<P>
Traffic accidents kill some 3,000 people and injure about
30,000 others in Greece each year. 
</P>
