<HEADLINE> One Killed in Car Explosion Near Ramallah </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 29 (Xinhua) -- A car loaded with large
amounts of explosives blew up Tuesday near the West Bank city of
Ramallah, killing a Palestinian and wounding two others,
Palestinian police said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion went off in an industrial area of Beitunia near
Ramallah at about 1:30 p.m. local time and the force of the blast
mangled and cut the car in half, the police added.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian killed in the explosion was identified as
Zahran Ibrahim, 35, from the West Bank village of Biddou. The two
injured men, brothers from Biddou village, were taken to a
Ramallah hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The scene of the explosion was not far from where the body of
Hamas (Islamic Resistance Movement) bombmaker Mohiyedine Sharif
was found several month ago after a car explosion.
</P>
<P>
So far nobody has claimed responsibility for the explosion
and the Palestinian police are investigating the incident.
</P>
