<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Renovate Roads in East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Roads
Authority announced Tuesday that it has plans to renovate 1,258
kilometers of roads in eastern parts of the country this year at
a cost of 11.3 million Birr (1.6 million U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Ahmed Kedir, acting head of the authority's district office in
Dire Dawa Town, told local press that the authority has finalized
preparations to renovate 425 kilometers of asphalt road and 833
kilometers of gravel road in the stated period.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that the Metehara-Mile, Awash-Jijiga, Dire
Dawa-Dewele, Arberikite-Metehara and Babile-Fike roads are among
the major highways that the authority envisages to maintain.
</P>
<P>
The authority renovated 1,128 kilometers of roads in eastern
parts of the country last year at a cost of 9.8 million Birr (1.4
million U.S. Dollars), according to the official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
