<HEADLINE> Israel to Impose Full Closure on Palestinian Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Israel will impose full
closure on the West Bank and Gaza Strip over Yom Kippur (Day of
Atonement), the most important holiday on the Jewish calendar,
Israel Radio reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The closure on the Palestinian areas, which will bar more than
2.5 million Palestinians including tens of thousands of workers
from entering Israe, will start on Tuesday afternoon and last
until 1 o'clock on Thursday morning, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The holiday will begin at sundown Tuesday and end at sundown
Wednesday. The Jews are expected, on this day, to pray, fast and
ask God for forgiveness for their sins.
</P>
<P>
Israeli security forces will continually be on high alert
throughout the country in the holiday and troops will provide
backup to the police forces in the major cities. In addition,
synagogues in the country will be protected by the civil guard
units.
</P>
<P>
Israel routinely seals off its borders with the Palestinian
areas during Jewish holidays in a bid to avoid terrorist attacks.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, since Israeli troops killed two activists of the
Islamic militant group Hamas early this month, Hamas has
threatened to revenge and Israeli security forces have been on
alert. 
</P>
</TEXT>
