<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Prepares for Aging Society </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- China will launch a series of
old people-friendly projects and hold symposiums on the aging
problem during the forthcoming International Year of Old Persons.
</P>
<P>
The International Year of Old Persons with the theme of
"Towards a Society for All Ages" was scheduled by the United
Nations General Assembly in 1997. It will start on October 1,
1998, said Zhang Wenfan, president of the Chinese Old Citizens
Association.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that to follow the theme, China will try to build a
society, which will be developed with concerted efforts of the old
and young and enjoyed by all.
</P>
<P>
China will become an aging country by the year 2000, when 130
million people will reach the age of 60, making up over
one-tenth of the total population.
</P>
<P>
"It is ten years earlier than the time when the whole world
enters the aging society in 2010," said Prof. Zhang Xianqiao with
the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences, adding that by the year
2040, the aged population will grow to 25 percent of China's
population.
</P>
<P>
"The aging process of Chinese society will only take 13 years,
much faster than that in developed countries, which was 50 to
80 years," Prof. Zhang said. "This will apply more pressures to
China in dealing with the aging problem."
</P>
<P>
The number of senior citizens above the age of 80 in China has
almost doubled since the early 1980s, because of the extended
average life expectancy, he said. As a result, the government as
well as individuals have become more concerned with taking care of
 the aged.
</P>
<P>
Special apartments and other social service centers for the the
aged are mushrooming in big cities of Shanghai, Beijing and
Tianjin cities and Jiangsu, Zhejiang, Shandong, Hunan and Sichuan
Provinces which have already entered the aged society,
</P>
<P>
Activities will be conducted between the traditional Chinese
festivals for the old persons in October in 1998 and 1999 to mark
the International Year for the Old Persons, said Zhang Wenfan.
</P>
<P>
The activities, which will include symposiums on the policies
for aging society and various projects to aid senior citizens, are
designed to promote the drive to respect and love old
people and solve the aging problem, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
