<HEADLINE> Plane Accident "Big Shock": Cape Verde PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Cape Verde Prime Minister
Carlos Veiga Tuesday described the air accident he experienced
Monday as "a big shock."
</P>
<P>
When his plane touched down at Praia airport in the capital of
Cape Verde Monday there was an accident in which Veiga was
wounded and one of his bodyguards killed, the Angolan News Agency
Angog reported.
</P>
<P>
In a short statement released from a hospital in the capital
Praia, Veiga said, "that was a great shock and I was lucky to
survive. My condition is fine right now, and what I need is to
stay in hospital for observation."
</P>
<P>
He said, "it is a pity to lose Pascoal de Oliveria Gomes, my
bodyguard who had followed me since 1990. That is a great loss to
his family, and I lost a companion, for which I shall be sad
forever."
</P>
<P>
Referring to the accident, he stressed that it was the calm
and sober crew who had "saved the lives of the rest on the plane
and avoided a bigger tragedy."
</P>
<P>
Veiga was on his way back home from Saint Nicolau city on a
twinotter Monday morning. Some sources said there was a strong
wind and visibility very low around the airport when the accident
happened. 
