<HEADLINE> Kenya Expects More Investment, Tourists from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan Minister for Lands
and Settlement K. Ngala said Tuesday that his country is
expecting more investment and tourists from China as their
cordial bilateral relations move forward.
</P>
<P>
"Kenya invites the Chinese business community... to invest in
our country directly or through joint ventures," Ngala said at
the reception at the Chinese Embassy here Tuesday to mark the
