extended loans and grants to Kenya for development in the areas
of intrastructure, sports facilities and institutions of health
and higher learning," Ngala noted.
</P>
<P>
"China and Kenya maintain warm and friendly relations," the
minister noted with satisfaction.
</P>
<P>
At the reception, Chinese Ambassador to Kenya An Yongyu also
said that the two countries have enjoyed a cordial and
long-standing relationship dating back to hundreds of years ago.
</P>
<P>
China attaches much importance to its ties with Kenya which is
an active member of the currently 15-strong U.N. Security
Council, the Organization of African Union and the East African
Cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Kenya and China set up official diplomatic relations on
December 14, 1963, two days after this east African country
declared independence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
