<HEADLINE> UNECA to Set Up Electronic Information Center in Zambia  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Economic
Commission for Africa (UNECA) is to spend more than 100,000 U.S.
sub-regional development office in Lusaka, Zambia.
</P>
<P>
UNECA acting director Robert Okello said in an interview here
Monday that the initiative was intended to facilitate information
sharing among all sub-regional offices and the headquarters in
Ethiopia, Times of Zambia said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The information center which is expected to be operational by
mid next year will be linked to Zamtel, a local government-owned
telecommunication company, and will be done through radio and
satellite, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
"We are trying to set up the center because we need to share
information between sub-regional offices and our headquarters in
Addis Ababa," Okello said.
</P>
<P>
Presently the UNECA information center at the local
sub-regional office situated in Lusaka operates manually which
has created some communication problems.
</P>
<P>
The local office has been operational since 1966 and has since
worked in collaboration with various organizations in capacity
building.
</P>
<P>
The organizations that have benefited from the information
center include the Lusaka-based Common Market for Eastern and
Southern Africa (COMESA) and Southern Africa Management
Institute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
