<HEADLINE> Iran, Iraq Swap Remains of Killed Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Iran and Iraq on Tuesday
swapped remains of 111 Iranian and 117 Iraqi soldiers killed
during the 1980-88 war between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the official news agency IRNA, the exchange took
place at the border point of Shalamcheh, Iran's southwestern
province of Khuzestan.
</P>
<P>
Mir Baqerzadeh, an Iranian official in charge of the committee
of searching for those missing in actions, said that the remains
of Iranian soldiers were found in Iraq's Shalamcheh region and 77
of them had clear identities.
</P>
<P>
The exchange came after a meeting between Iranian and Iraqi
officials in Basra, southern Iraq on Monday, on how to step up the
search for missing Iranian and Iraqi soldiers.
</P>
<P>
It was the third exchange of remains of killed soldiers
between Iran and Iraq since they started joint searching
operations in May.
</P>
<P>
They exchanged remains of 53 Iranians with 134 Iraqis in June
and 100 Iranians with 83 Iraqis in July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
