<HEADLINE> Share Prices Extend Gains on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Share prices extended gains
on the Singapore Stock Market Tuesday as widespread expectation of
an imminent cut in U.S. interest rates lifted market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) went up 7.98 points to
end at 938.51 points.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover was 118.86 million units valued at 209.26
million Singapore dollars (124.57 million U.S. dollars). Advancers
led decliners by 96 to 56 with 239 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
OUB F was the most active stock of the day as it had a
turnover of 12.02 million stocks traded. It was followed by
KepLand that had 9.90 million units done. KepCorp was next with
9.19 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
DBS F led the increase of the day as it rose by 45 cents to
6.60 Singapore dollar at close. UOB F moved up 30 cents to finish
at 5.00 Singapore dollars. OCBC F edged up 22 cents to end at 4.06
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser of the day
as it lost 30 cents to close at 13.60 Singapore dollars. Nat Kep
dropped 20 cents to finish at 0.50 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sem
shed off 20 cents as well and ended at 6.05 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said a cut in U.S. interest rates will likely lead to
a decline in global interest rates, which would benefit equity
markets.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that investors will eye the U.S. Federal Reserve
Open Market Committee's meeting due to be held later Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, members are expected to vote for a cut in the
Benchmark Federal funds rates, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
