<HEADLINE> Office in Macao to Issue Portuguese Passports, ID Cards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The preparatory office of the
future Portuguese Consulate General in Macao will begin issuing
Portuguese passports and identification cards in November.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Frota, the office's director, was quoted by the
Portuguese news agency Lusa as saying that the new measure is
meant to ensure a "smooth transition" of certain functions from
the Macao government to the future consular general.
</P>
<P>
In this way, future consular members will also have a chance to
get familiar with such services, so that the consulate general can
better carry out its work after Macao's handover in December next
year, he said.
</P>
<P>
Portuguese passports and ID cards are currently issued by the
Macao government's Identification Services Department.
</P>
<P>
The future Portuguese consulate-general in Macao will have 30
members of staff, according to Lusa. 
