<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seventy-six Percent of Indian Women Abused: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 29 (Xinhua) -- At least 76 percent of
India's women suffer from some form of sexual abuse, of them 40
percent by family members and 31 percent by known persons.
</P>
<P>
The abusers within the family include maternal and paternal
uncles and male cousins (42 percent), according to an extensive
survey conducted by Recovering and Health from Incest (RAHI), a
Delhi-based women's support group.
</P>
<P>
Fathers and brothers, male neighbors and family friends, and
even servants were also listed as abusers by the survey published
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The study, "Voices from Silent Zone," is based on experiences
of incest and childhood sexual abuse of 600 middle and upper
middle class Indian women.
</P>
<P>
Respondents recalled their confusion, anger, disgust,
helplessness, fear, shame, humiliation, guilt and self-blame at
being abused by persons they trusted.
</P>
<P>
The survey gave details of some women who were abused since
their childhood.
</P>
<P>
A 35-year-old advertising professional had been abused by her
paternal uncle, male cousin and two male domestic servants between
the ages of 4 and 6, 8 and 22.
</P>
<P>
"I was abused from 8 years onwards everyday in the summer
holidays, from 16 years onwards almost everyday till I was 18,"
she said.
</P>
<P>
The study revealed that the earliest age at which a woman
recalled being abused was only 2. One of the respondents recalled
being abused even in the nursery.
</P>
<P>
"Almost 50 percent of the abuse has taken place below the age
of 12 years and 49 percent above 12," said Anuja Gupta, director
of RAHI. "The abuse clearly spans almost half a century and is
spread over different kinds of family systems."
</P>
<P>
The study is said to be the first in the country to have such a
vast data bank from the middle and upper middle class.
</P>
<P>
The report also throws light on the background of the
respondents, who were broadly divided into 7 categories in terms
of their occupation.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-five percent of the respondents were students, the
remaining were a mix of employed women and housewives.
</P>
<P>
It claimed that 73 percent of the respondents were between the
ages of 18 to 25, whereas 22 percent were above the age of 25 and
5 percent below the age of 18. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980929.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice Premier Meets Overseas Chinese Scholars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Qian
Qichen today met with some 40 noted overseas scholars of Chinese
origin.
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed welcome to the scholars, who arrived in Beijing
on the eve of the National Day, adding that he hoped that they
will play a greater role in China's moderization drive.
</P>
<P>
Qian also briefed the guests on anti-flood campaign in summer.
</P>
<P>
Luke C. L. Yuan, a famous physician now residing in the United
States, said that all overseas scholars of Chinese origin are
proud of every achievement made by China and are willing to
contribute more China.
</P>
<P>
Guo Dongpo, director of the Office of Overseas Chinese Affairs
of the State Council, was present at the meeting. 
</P>
