<HEADLINE> Abubakar to Visit Middle East, Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Head of State Gen.
Abdulsalami Abubakar is to visit the Middle East and Asia next
month following his recent visit to Britain, the United States
and France.
</P>
<P>
The list of Middle East countries to be visited by Gen.
Abubakar is in the discussion with Egypt featuring prominently,
This Day newspaper quoted presidency sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that "we are still fine-tuning the list of
countries as consultations are yet to be concluded."
</P>
<P>
Following his Middle East trip, the Nigerian head of state is
scheduled to visit Asia and one of the countries Gen. Abubakar is
set to visit is Japan, the sources noted.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the reasons for the Middle East and Asia trip,
the sources said that Gen. Abubakar is determined to return
Nigeria to the mainstream of the community of nations as a
respectful country.
</P>
<P>
So far, Gen. Abubakar has visited South Africa, Niger, Benin,
Britain, the United States and France since he took office last
June. 
