<HEADLINE> China Protects Lives of Nationals in Lesotho </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman Tang Guoqiang said that Chinese government keeps close
touch with the governments of Lesotho and South Africa so as to
protect the lives and property of the Chinese nationals residing
in Lesotho.
</P>
<P>
Tang made the remark at today's regular press conference when
asked to comment on the fact that the Chinese personnel and
nationals in that country have been disturbed by the recent war
there.
</P>
<P>
He said that 400 Chinese nationals and officials took refuge in
South Africa on September 22.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese government has required Lesotho
authorities to take effective measures to ensure the safety of the
Chinese nationals and personnel, and asked South African
authorities to provide necessary assistance in issuing passports
to Chinese who are in urgent need of entering its territories.
</P>
<P>
Chinese diplomatic officials in these two countries have
promptly visited the Chinese taking refuge and provided them
with relief goods.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that to date, there has been no report on casualties
of Chinese nationals and personnel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
