<HEADLINE> 2 French Warships to Visit Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The French supply and
command ship "La Somme" (flagship) and the frigate "La Fayette"
will arrive here on Saturday for a five-day courtesy call, the
English daily Kuwait Times reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two warships will anchor at the Shuwaikh Port which is
close to Kuwait City, according to the daily.
</P>
<P>
"The fleet will come here with the aim to reinforce the
friendly relations between Kuwait and France," the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Launched in 1995, frigate La Fayette is a multipurpose stealth
frigate, which has a displacement of 3,600 tonnes, a crew of 155
and is the first of a six vessel-fleet under command of the French
national navy.
</P>
<P>
La Fayette is armed with surface to surface missiles MM40
Exocet and has the facility for a possible installation of a
surface to air anti-missile system and anti-ship missiles.
</P>
<P>
Rear Admiral Jean-Louis Battet, who commands the French naval
forces deployed in the Indian ocean, and his staff will be on
board the command ship. He will meet a number of civilian and
military personnel during the visit.
</P>
<P>
A number of activities will be organized on board such as a
press conference and a presentation of ships to Kuwaiti officers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
