<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Objects Iraq's Return in Arab Sports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 29 (Xinhua) -- A senior Kuwaiti sports
official said Kuwait will stand against all attempts that aim at
bringing Iraq back to Arab sports events, a local Arabic daily
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Kuwaiti Olympic Committee and the Kuwaiti
Soccer Federation, Sheikh Ahmad Al-Fahd said in an interview with
Al-Anba that "Kuwait's position is clear and no one has the rights
to overlook Kuwait's rights."
</P>
<P>
There were news reports saying Kuwait has accepted Iraq's
participation in the upcoming Arab Cup Soccer Tournament to be
hosted in Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Ahmad said that Iraq, which invaded and occupied Kuwait in
1990-1991, can only return to Arab sports events after
implementing all United Nations resolutions, including the release
of Kuwait's prisoners of war (POW) and detainees.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait claimed that Iraq is still holding about 600 Kuwait's
POWs, an allegation that the Iraqis denied.
</P>
<P>
"We will not shake hands stained with blood before they return
to us all rights," Ahmad said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
