<HEADLINE> EU Program Targets Kenyan Exporters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan exporters are
expected to benefit from an European Commission-funded program
aimed at improving the quality and diversity of their products.
</P>
<P>
The program will initially concentrate on companies dealing in
horticulture, meat and fish products, packaging materials,
processed foods, agricultural inputs, machinery and equipment,
the Daily Nation newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It aims "to assist Kenyan companies to add value to their
traditional and manufactured exports," said Peter Muthoka, chief
of Kenya's Export Promotion Council (EPC).
</P>
<P>
The program will be administered through six national trade
bodies -- the Federation of Kenya Employers, Kenya Association of
Manufacturers, Fresh Produce Exporters Association of Kenya,
Kenya Fish Exporters Association and the Kenya National Chamber
of Commerce and Industry.
</P>
<P>
Muthoka also called for more private companies to participate
in the project so as to promote Kenya's share in the European
Union market.
</P>
<P>
The EPC will intensify its activities to promote Kenya as a
source of high quality goods and a good investment opportunity,
especially for the emerging markets, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
