<HEADLINE> China's Foreign Experts Get "Friendship Award" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government
conferred its "Friendship Award" on 46 foreign experts working in
China here today.
</P>
<P>
China invites more than 80,000 foreign experts to work in
universities, scientific research institutes, industrial and
agricultural departments, state key construction projects, and
joint ventures every year.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen said at the awards ceremony that the
enormous achievements in China's economic and social development
would have been impossible without the hard work of all the
foreign experts, experts from overseas with Chinese origin, and
international friends working in China.
</P>
<P>
China welcomes more foreign experts, experts from overseas with
Chinese origin, and international friends to participate in
China's modernization, reforms, and opening up in various ways,
Qian said.
</P>
<P>
Since the "Friendship Award" established in 1991. about 420
foreign experts have received the award. This year's 46 recipients
come from Australia, Austria, Japan, Singapore, the United States,
Germany, and 13 other countries.  
