<HEADLINE> Bank of China Sponsors APEC Business Summit 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Bank of China Tuesday
signed on as a platinum sponsor in support of the APEC
(Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation) Business summit 1998 to be
held in Kuala Lumpur on November 14-16.
</P>
<P>
Bank of China, the leading bank in China, committed a
contribution of 200,000 U.S. dollars under the sponsorship
agreement signed here Tuesday by Abdullah Mat Zaid and Shafiq Sit
Abdullah, Co-chairs of APEC, and Du Chaohua, deputy general
manager of the bank's international department.
</P>
<P>
Bank of China is the sixth platinum sponsor. Five other
platinum sponsors are from the United States and Chinese Taipei.
</P>
<P>
Shafiq said on the occasion, "With Bank of China moving
strongly towards a more visible participative role in the region,
we are confident that its role in the summit will help provide
constructive solution to current regional economic contagion."
</P>
<P>
Abdullah also praised Bank of China for the sponsorship, saying
Bank of China's decision to sponsor the summit will augur well
particularly at a time when a demonstration of commitment to
Malaysia and Asia during this period of economic uncertainty will
go a long way in promoting a stronger foundation for the future.
</P>
<P>
Du said, "We believe that the upcoming APEC and its Business
Summit 1998 will render positive influences in finding solutions
to the regional and global problems by means of promoting the
exchange of views between the related governments themselves, the
government and corporations, and the corporations themselves. We
sponsor this summit with an aim to promote such exchanges."
</P>
</TEXT>
