<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, September 29 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- Former Malaysian Deputy Prime Minister and
Finance Minister Anwar Ibrahim pleaded not guilty in the Sessions
Court here Tuesday to five charges of corruption and four for
committing sodomy.
</P>
<P>
Anwar, who was produced in Sessions Court 4 at the Jalan Raja
courts complex here Tuesday noon, replied "tidak bersalah, mohon
dibicara" (not guilty, I claim trial) to each charge when the
court interpreter read out the charges one by one to him and each
time he was asked to enter his plea. (Malaysia-Anwar)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Albanian Socialist Prime Minister Fatos Nano has
handed in his resignation to President Rexhep Mejdani, Socialist
Party spokesman Musa Ulqini said on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the party leadership asked the steering
council of the Socialist Party to propose its secretary-general
Pandeli Majko as candidate for prime minister. The council is
expected to discuss the nomination on Tuesday.
(Albania-PM-Resignation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- The Serbian parliament approved a resolution on the
Kosovo crisis put forward by the Serbian government at a special
session Monday.
</P>
<P>
The resolution, which appealed again to Kosovo ethnic Albanians
to resume talks with the Serbian government, said that the Kosovo
problem has its roots in the ethnic Albanian separatists who try
to separate Kosovo from Serbia. It firmly supported the
government's measures on maintaining the territorial integrity of
the Serbian Republic and Yugoslavia and on fight against
terrorism. (Serbia-Parliament)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Serbian police have reportedly killed more than 100
Kosovo Liberation Army fighters and arrested hundreds of armed
ethnic Albanians in conflicts over the last two weeks.
</P>
<P>
The Pristina Information Center said Monday that Serbian police
attacked and destroyed ethnic Albanian strongholds in Drenica and
Cicavica last week. (Kosovo-Conflicts) 
</P>
