<HEADLINE> China's Construction Bank Supporting Housing Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank
(CCB) has offered support for the state's "affordable housing
project" by providing 34.4 billion yuan in loans to build
affordable housing.
</P>
<P>
The figure accounts for 48.4 percent of the state's planned
loans for the project, the bank said today.
</P>
<P>
CCB sources say that since the project began in 1995, the CCB
has been a leader in housing financing. By August, the bank had
loaned 16.3 billion yuan for 761 housing development projects with
a total area of 48.24 million sq.m.
</P>
<P>
The CCB has been offering various housing financial services
over the past few years, mainly in housing development loans and
individual housing loans, which have helped push the construction
of affordable housing and the individual housing loan business.
</P>
<P>
By the end of August, the CCB's had 50.7 billion yuan in
individual housing loans, 17.3 billion yuan of that loaned this
year. The bank has helped 1.89 million families buy houses.
</P>
