<HEADLINE> France's Carrefour Interested In China Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, September 29 (Xinhua) -- France's worldwide supermarket
chain Carrefour plans to open its ninth supermarket in China in
the city of Zhuhai, in southern Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of Communications Zhuhai branch will provide 100 million
yuan in loans for the new supermarket.
</P>
<P>
The group plans to open five more supermarkets in China by the
end of the year, giving Carrefour 14 supermarkets in China by the
end of the year. Its first store in China was in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The 14 supermarkets will cover more than 100,000 square meters
of floor space and are expected to bring in about two billion yuan
in business a year.
</P>
<P>
Carrefour's first supermarket in southern China opened in
1996 in Shenzhen. It had 152 million yuan in business during the
first half of this year and has become one of the busiest
supermarkets there.
</P>
<P>
China's large population, stable economic growth, and increase
in incomes are encouraging, according to Andre Charbonel, general
manager of Carrefour's businesses in southern China.  
</P>
