<HEADLINE> China Sticks to RMB Convertibility under Current Account </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- China will stick to the
convertibility of its currency under current account, Wu Xiaoling,
director of the State Administration of Foreign Exchange (SAFE),
said today.
</P>
<P>
He told a press conference that China will guarantee supply of
foreign exchange for legal transactions, debt repayment and the
normal capital flow.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, he said that China will crack down on the
illegal capital flow in foreign currencies so as to safeguard the
stability of RMB and the interests of investors.
</P>
<P>
He said that China has adopted stricter procedures on
verification of foreign exchange used for current account
transactions so as to eliminate fraud.
</P>
<P>
He said that China has also taken measures to tighten control
over its currency and protect the interests of investors. 
</P>
