<HEADLINE> High-Tech Achievement Fair In Southern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The city of Shenzhen in
China's Guangdong Province will have high-tech achievements fairs
annually, starting next year.
</P>
<P>
They will be held in cooperation with three Chinese ministries
and the Chinese Academy of Sciences to exhibit high-tech
achievements and applications as well as export goods from
Shenzhen and the Pearl River Delta.
</P>
<P>
The fair is expected to compete with the China Export
Commodities Fair in Guangzhou, giving Guangdong Province two major
international fairs. The city has been building an exhibition hall
with at least 20,000 sq.m. of floor space.
</P>
<P>
High-tech industries have been growing rapidly in Shenzhen in
recent years and have become a major economic force, with 77.6
billion yuan in output value last year, accounting for 56 percent
of the city's total industrial output value.  
</P>
</TEXT>
