<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share
market closed lower here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 12 points lower at 1,705 with a turnover
 of 65 million NZ dollars (32.6 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the major leaders, AMP plumped 85 cents to 2450 cents.
Telecom lost 7 cents to 745 cents, Carter Holt Harvey 5 cents to
128 cents, Auckland Airport 3 cents to 182 cents, and Fletcher
Energy also 3 cents to 295 cents. Air New Zealand, Fletcher Forest
and Fletcher paper eased 1 cent each to 142 cents, 42 cents and
99 cents respectively.
</P>
<P>
Brierley Investments edged up 2 cents to 37 cents while
Fletcher Building closed stable at 193 cents. 
</P>
