<HEADLINE> China Developing Coal Gas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- China is speeding up the
development of coal gas as a major new energy source with a series
of preferential loan policies and fee exemptions.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior Coal Industry Administration official,
the government will not collect compensation fees for exploitation
of coal gas resources for the initial stage of development, and
loans will be made available for key coal gas projects.
</P>
<P>
China has given priority to coal gas to make up for shortfalls
in the energy supply. The increased use of coal gas is expected to
improve the energy resource structure, reduce air pollution, and
make production safer.
</P>
<P>
China is rich in coal gas resources. Coal fields in the
northern, northeastern and southern parts of China are estimated
to have 3.5 billion cu.m. of recoverable resources.
</P>
<P>
The country has had over 50 coal gas projects, including a
650,000-cu.m. gas storage tank and a total of 620,000-meter-long
coal gas pipeline.
</P>
<P>
The administration source says that the national annual
utilization of coal gas is more than 400 million cu.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980929.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Popular Chinese Pop Singer Fined for Tax Evasion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- China announced today that
its tax administrative department has imposed a fine of 813,000
million yuan on the pop singer Mao A'min for not paying 271,000
million yuan in taxes from 1994 to 1996.
</P>
<P>
The tax department completed its investigation of Mao's case,
but the judicial department will look into the matter further and
the possible involvement of other persons.
</P>
<P>
Mao and people she works with will have to pay a total of 3.33
million yuan, which includes back taxes, the fine, some fines
levied on associates, and interest on overdue taxes.
</P>
<P>
Mao was fined once before for tax evasion in 1989. The tax
department study this time showed that from January 1994 to March
1996, she and her associates failed to pay 1.06 million yuan in
taxes levied on profits from 109 performances in 13 provinces.
</P>
<P>
An open hearing on Mao's case was held today in the city of
Jiaxing in Zhejiang Province, where the tax evasion charge is
being adjudicated, at the request of Mao's agent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980929.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Malaysian Deputy PM Pleads Not Guilty at Court </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Former Malaysian deputy
prime minister and finance minister Anwar Ibrahim pleaded not
guilty in the Sessions Court here Tuesday to five charges of
corruption and four for committing sodomy.
</P>
<P>
Anwar, who was produced in Sessions Court 4 at the Jalan Raja
courts complex here Tuesday noon, replied "tidak bersalah, mohon
dibicara" (not guilty, I claim trial) to each charge when the
court interpreter read out the charges one by one to him and each
time he was asked to enter his plea.
</P>
<P>
Judge Puan Hasnah Mohd Hashim presided over the proceedings.
The prosecution was headed by senior deputy public prosecutor
Abdul Gani Patail while Anwar had seven lawyers led by Raja Aziz
Addruse to represent him.
</P>
<P>
Present in court were Anwar's wife Wan Azizah Wan Ismail, his
father Ibrahim Abdul Rahman and his father-in-law Wan Ismail as
well as his two daughters.
</P>
<P>
Clad in brown pants and a checkered shirt, Anwar was smiling as
he entered the courtroom. He then embraced his wife, his daughters
and his father.
</P>
<P>
Judge Puan Hasnah later granted an application by the
prosecution to transfer the case for hearing at the High Court.
</P>
<P>
Anwar was arrested by police on September 20 under the Internal
Security Act following riots by his supporters here.
</P>
<P>
Prior to his arrest, Anwar was implicated in two cases of
committing unnatural sex act when his adopted brother and a male
friend confessed in court that they had been sodomized by him.
</P>
<P>
Besides the nine charges mentioned at the court here, one more
charge of unnatural sex act against Anwar will be mentioned at the
Petaling Jaya court near here Wednesday, according to an
announcement by the Attorney-General's Chambers earlier Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement signed by Special Officer to the
Attorney- General, Shamsuddin Hassan, the attorney-general as the
public prosecutor was satisfied that there was sufficient "prima
facie" evidence to charge Anwar for the offenses.
</P>
<P>
Anwar was sacked as deputy prime minister and minister of
finance on September 2 and expelled from the ruling United Malays
National Organization (UMNO) the following day for "low morals".
</P>
<P>
Anwar's supporters had held several illegal assemblies in the
Jalan Raja courthouse area here since his detention forcing police
to impose tight security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
