<HEADLINE> Jordan Cheers Sosa in Home-Run Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Michael Jordan, who
wearing a Chicago Cubs jacket, encouraged Sammy Sosa to increase
his 66 home runs in his last games Monday night.
</P>
<P>
Jordan was greeted with a huge roar when he trotted out to the
mound to throw out the first pitch. The cheers grew even louder
when Jordan shed the jacket and turned around to show everyone
that he wearing Sosa's No. 21 jersey.
</P>
<P>
Jordan is not only a big baseball fan, but also played minor
league baseball for a season during his brief retirement from
basketball.
</P>
<P>
Jordan walked off the mound laughing as he greeted Sosa with a
hug. The two have become friends during Sosa's spectacular season.
</P>
<P>
With 70 home runs Mark McGwire has surpassed Sosa by four
home-runs.
</P>
<P>
"I've been saying all year that he's "The Man," Sosa said
Sunday. "But Mark McGwire is going to go home, and maybe go to
the beach. And I'm going to play."
</P>
<P>
McGwire hit five homers in his last three games to finish with
a total of 70. Sosa has an one more game but is difficult to
catch up. 
</P>
