<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mining Causes Geological Damage at Taxco </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Gold, silver and tin
mining has threatened one of Mexico's main tourist destinations as
land sinks and buildings crack under the strain.
</P>
<P>
Residents of the city of Taxco, in the state of Guerrero, fear
the situation could result in a tragedy unless they are
compensated for the damage.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, evidence of cracking and flooding in southern
Taxco neighborhoods has appeared, and the residents blame the
misuse of explosives by mining companies, the government news agency
Notimex reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In some areas, the ground has subsided by 20 meters. so far no
deaths or injuries have been reported but dozens of inhabitants
fear "a great disaster" is in the making, said Notimex.
</P>
<P>
Romeo Aleman Serrano, leader of the affected group of
households, said his group had sent letters to state governor
Angel Aguirre Rivero, asking for compensation from the mining
companies for the damage and demanding that the area be declared
hazardous.
</P>
<P>
The city of Taxco, 175 kilometers south of Mexico city, was
founded in 1528 by the Spanish, and is internationally known by
its handicrafts, architecture and silver works. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
