<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spanish King Urges Alliance For Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Spanish King Juan Carlos Monday
urged Italian business leaders to extend trade ties with Spain to
help promote development in the backward parts of both countries
and the entire Mediterranean basin.
</P>
<P>
Carlos, on a five-day trip to Italy which began with an early
afternoon meeting with Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro,
called for new Italo-Spanish business initiatives to help reduce
the unemployment "which afflicts our countries".
</P>
<P>
"Economic collaboration between the Italian and Iberian
peninsulas has a 20-century tradition," Carlos told the gathering
of top businessmen, noting that Italy was Spain's third largest
trade partner.
</P>
<P>
"Today there is a strong desire to find areas of cooperation
that prevail over the possible difficulties linked to our
respective economic interests," Carlos added.
</P>
<P>
The king, who was born in Italy 60 years ago, said the two
economies could be made to complement each other for the good of
the whole Mediterranean region.
</P>
<P>
Spain's economy was less saturated, cheaper and had good
penetration into some non-European Union regions, while Italy's
was more flexible and innovative and had a great capacity to meet
demand, Carlos said.
</P>
<P>
Along with Queen Sofia, he is on his second official visit to
Italy. During his tour, he will become the first foreign head of
state to address the Italian Senate and Chamber of Deputies (lower
house).
</P>
<P>
The royals will also visit Naples and Palermo. During their
stay, they will meet Italian leaders and attend a string of
cultural events. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
