<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Hopes Bonn to Keep Push for European Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sofia, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian leaders said Monday
that they hoped Germany would continue to be a driving power for
European integration and European Union (EU) expansion.
</P>
<P>
In a telegram of congratulations to Gerhard Schroeder, leader
of the German Social Democratic Party (SDP), who toppled Helmut
Kohl in Sunday's election to become Germany's chancellor,
Bulgarian President Peter Stoyanov said the election victory would
enable the SDP to strengthen Germany's role as a major factor in
world politics.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that your efforts will help Germany continue to be a
driving power of European integration, including EU expansion, and
that your support will enable NATO to activate its open-door
policies," Stoyanov said.
</P>
<P>
The president also hoped that the victory would open up a new
stage in the traditionally good Bulgarian-German relations.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian Prime Minister Ivan Kostov said, "The development of
relations with Germany are based on a very strong legal framework
and we expect them to progress further."
</P>
<P>
He said that Bulgarian Foreign Minister Nadezhda Mihailova
would visit Germany soon.
</P>
<P>
Mihailova said at a regular Council of Ministers' meeting on
Monday that she firmly believed that the relations between the two
countries would remain good and joint projects already agreed
would be implemented.
</P>
<P>
"Schroeder's statement on the eve of the elections provided
grounds to be optimistic that relations between Bulgaria and
Germany will remain good," the foreign minister said.
</P>
<P>
Justice Minister Vassil Gotsev said that Bulgaria would
maintain the same good relations with Germany led by Schroeder as
that it had with the Germany led by Kohl.
</P>
<P>
The minister said, "I can say Germany realizes very well the
need for EU expansion, including Bulgaria, as well as the need for
this country to become a NATO member in view of security in the
Balkans." 
</P>
</TEXT>
