<HEADLINE> Romania's Agricultural Output Falls This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Romania's grain output is
expected to amount to 14 million tons this year, a 6-7 percent
drop from the average of the past few years, due to floods and
drought.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by Minister of Agriculture and Food
Industries Dinu Gavrilescu on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Gavrilescu said fruit output would also decrease by 25 percent
from last year.
</P>
<P>
He added the number of cattle had fallen from 1997's 3.7
million to the 3.5 million, pigs from 9.2 million to 9 million and
sheep from 11.6 million to 10 million.
</P>
<P>
Experts attributed the drop in animal husbandry to the
disbandment or bankruptcy of state-owned farms during their
restructuring.
</P>
<P>
However, Gavrilescu believed reduction of agricultural output
has not threatened the normal supply in Romania's domestic market
so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
