SINGAPORE -- Singapore's manufacturing output in August 1998
fell by 6.6 percent compared with a year ago, keeping a downturn
in all major clusters -- electronics, engineering and chemical,
the country's Economic Development Board (EDB) said Monday.
</P>
<P>
In the accumulative output for the first eight months of this
year, the electronics cluster registered a 3.4 percent decline
than a year ago while chemicals and engineering clusters enjoyed
12.9 and 3.6 percent increases respectively, the EDB
said. (Singapore-Manufacturing Output)
</P>
