<HEADLINE> World Bank Loans In North China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, September 29 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi Province
has used World Bank loans for 18 projects in the past 14 years,
according to figures released here today.
</P>
<P>
The province used 746 million U.S. dollars worth of loans for
water and soil conservation, forestry, animal husbandry, rural
highway construction, and farm produce processing.
</P>
<P>
World Bank officials say they are satisfied with the results of
the loans in Shanxi and used the province as a good example of
water and soil conservation projects.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi had a massive water and soil conservation project with
the loans on the loess plateau from 1994 to June, 1998 and raised
the vegetation from 19 percent to 24 percent and increased grain
output and farmers' annual income by a big margin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
