<HEADLINE> Serbian Parliament Passes Resolution on Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The Serbian parliament
approved a resolution on the Kosovo crisis put forward by the
Serbian government at a special session Monday.
</P>
<P>
The resolution appealed again to Kosovo ethnic Albanians to
resume talks with the Serbian government.
</P>
<P>
It said the Kosovo problem has its roots in the ethnic Albanian
separatists who try to separate Kosovo from Serbia.
</P>
<P>
It firmly supported the government's measures on maintaining
the territorial integrity of the Serbian Republic and Yugoslavia
and on fight against terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Some countries have aided the Kosovo terrorists with money,
weapons and publicity and have also requested NATO (North Atlantic
Treaty Organization) to make military interference in Yugoslavia,
it noted.
</P>
<P>
It expressed indignation at these countries and others which
often abuse the U.N. organizations to adopt measures that directly
harmed the sovereignty of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The resolution said political means and dialogue are the only
way to solve the Kosovo crisis, adding talks between the
government and the Kosovo ethnic Albanians should be resumed
immediately and unconditionally.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav government said Monday evening that it fully
supports the parliament action on resolution, and expected the
Kosovo ethnic Albanians to respond to the call on talks as soon as
possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
