<HEADLINE> Housing Business Increase in Northern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, the largest port
city in northern China, did 4.6 billion yuan in the housing
business, with 1.84 million sq.m. sold in the first eight months
of this year.
</P>
<P>
The sold housing is 880,000 sq.m. than more that for the same
period of last year, and an all time high. Over 70 percent of the
buyers were individuals, who accounted for 1.3 million sq.m. of
that.
</P>
<P>
A municipal official in charge of the real estate sector
attributed the growth to the government policy that stopped the
distribution of housing this year and an urban plan of replacing
dangerous houses with new residential quarters.
</P>
<P>
Local banks issued 3.4 billion yuan in loans for resettlement
and 880 million yuan for mortgages in the first eight months.
</P>
