<HEADLINE> UN to Clear Landmines in Sri Lanka's Northern Peninsula </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 29, (Xinhua) -- A team of United Nations
experts will begin landmine clearing operations in Sri Lanka's
Northern Jaffna Peninsula by year end, according to the UN office
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Landmine clearing operations are already underway in limited
areas of Jaffna city, the office sources said.
</P>
<P>
This project is conducted under the auspices of the United
Nations Development Project on landmine clearing in the
re-settlement areas of the Jaffna peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the operation required long reaching
communication units which cover the entire Jaffna peninsula.
</P>
<P>
In addition to this equipment sniffer dogs and landmine
specialists will also be brought in for the operation, the sources
added.
</P>
<P>
The Jaffna Peninsula, which was once the stronghold of the
Tamil rebels fighting for separate state, was recaptured in May
1995 by the government troops who are making every effort to
stabilize the civil administration in the peninsula. 
</P>
