<HEADLINE> Panama Seizes 3 Million Pirate CDs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 28 (Xinhua) -- A District Attorney's
office in Panama seized more than 3 million pirate CDs, CD-roms
and microchips over the weekend, according to press reports Monday.
</P>
<P>
The pirate CDs were seized in a warehouse close to Tocumen
international airport in the capital in an operation said to be
the biggest in Latin America since the fight against discographic
piracy.
</P>
<P>
The cargo is related to another half a million pirate CDs
captured at Ciudad del Este, Paraguay, on August 9, 1998 and sent
from Panama.
</P>
<P>
Before the operation, the District Attorney's office had
captured 33,000 pirate CDs of Brazilian music.
</P>
<P>
In the next few days, technicians and specialists from Brazil,
Paraguay, the United States and Hong Kong will come to Panama to
collaborate with the investigation. 
</P>
