<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shortage of Funds for Protecting Chinba's Relics (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Local governments have come up with measures to protect the
state-level relics site since 1994, one of the which is the
"Protection Plan" setting the scope and site of the Yinxu area. It
also regulates construction work in the protection zone.
</P>
<P>
The Anyang city government has also passed the "Methods of Yinxu
Protection and Management", the first local regulation on
state-level relics sites in the country.
</P>
<P>
In the 1980s, the Anyang city government spent 3 million yuan
on a Yinxu exhibition center on the ruins of ancient palaces,
which has attracted a large number of visitors, but the lack of
money prevents the center from becoming better.
</P>
<P>
And, it will take a lot more money to develop all the
underground ruins to attract more tourists, local government
officials say.
</P>
<P>
Duan said that his bureau has worked out many protection plans
but that they are worried that the plans may remain just plans and
not be put into practice. He said that the Anyang city government
plans to build a Yinxu museum, but the project has been halted
because of shortage of money. Only a storehouse that cost four
million yuan has been built.
</P>
<P>
The city government also wants to rebuild 12 imperial tombs and
over 1,000 sacrificial pits in the Yinxu area and turn it into a
tomb museum, but they need 20 million yuan and can think of no way
to raise the money. 
</P>
</TEXT>
