<HEADLINE> Pirated Disc Production Line Seized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Public security personnel in
east China's Fujian Province seized 11 people suspected of disc
piracy in a recent sting operation.
</P>
<P>
Police in the coastal city of Quanzhou ferreted out a
production line churning out illegal compact discs valued at more
than 13 million yuan (about 1.57 million U.S. dollars) in a
residential village house, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
The public security organs seized more than 80,000 finished or
semi-finished pirated video discs together with 49 source discs
and five tons of raw production materials.
</P>
<P>
After investigation, the police discovered that the suspects
began their illegal operation in early August.
</P>
<P>
Rural laborers from Guangdong, Jiangxi and Hunan provinces were
hired to maintain an average daily output of over 30,000 bootleg
discs, officials said.  
