<HEADLINE> Brazil Reports GDP Growth in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's gross
domestic product (GDP) of 1997 amounted to 866.8 billion reales
(753.7 billion U.S. dollars), and its economy grew 3.68 percent,
Brazil's Geography and Statistics Institute (BGSI) reported on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to an official report released by the BGSI, in 1997,
the industrial sector, with 5.52 percent growth, was the pillar of
the economy, followed by the agriculture sector, with 2.6 percent
growth and service sector, with a 1.24 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
In industry, the automobile industry which played an important
role, grew 14.31 percent, and civil construction industry, 8.45
percent.
</P>
