<HEADLINE> Beijing Clears Away Deserted Bicycles, Tricycles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Beijing municipality recently
decided to clear away old bicycles and tricycles abandoned in
public places to keep the national capital clean and tidy.
</P>
<P>
Major traffic areas including crossroads, main traffic
arteries, lanes, residential neighborhoods, bus stops and airports
are all part of this campaign, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
Bicycles and tricycles that will be cleared away include those
without license plates and those that have been in the streets for
a long time. They will be gathered together at designated places
where they can be claimed within three months.
</P>
<P>
The government's decision was initiated by a report given after
investigations carried out by three middle-school students, who
are keen on environmental protection. They found more than 180
abandoned bikes in a residential area and over 80 in a bicycle
parking lot.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, sometimes called the "kingdom of bicycles," has about
seven million bikes, not counting the abandoned ones.  
</P>
</TEXT>
