<HEADLINE> Overseas-Funded Businesses In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
now ranks second in the country in the number of overseas-funded
enterprises, with more than 22,000, putting it just next to south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The first overseas-funded enterprise in Jiangsu was set up in
1981. Overseas-funded enterprises have brought in 71.6 billion
U.S. dollars of investment.
</P>
<P>
There are 1,625 overseas-funded enterprises with an investment
of more than 10 million U.S. dollars each and 175 with profits of
more than 10 million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu now has 76 overseas-invested enterprises with each
earning over 10 million U.S. dollars from export trade, and 3 such
firms with each earning over 100 million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
