<DOCNO> XIE19980929.0290 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Becoming Less Dependent On Wheat Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 29 (Xinhua) -- China will become less
dependent on the international market for high-quality wheat over
the next few years when a new wheat strain begins to be widely
used, Chinese wheat experts said here recently.
</P>
<P>
The new No. 906 wheat gives high yield, high quality, and is
resistant to common wheat diseases and drought.
</P>
<P>
The strain was developed by Shen Tianmin, a wheat breeding
expert in Henan Province after 18 years of research.
</P>
<P>
Laboratory tests show major indicators like protein and gluten
content and water absorption equal to national high-quality wheat
standards.
</P>
<P>
Experiments in Henan Province, a major wheat producer in the
country, resulted in a per-hectare yield of from 7,500 kg to 9,000
kg, which is 2,700 to 4,200 kg higher than ordinary strains.
</P>
<P>
Fan Lian, a wheat specialist, said that China imports 2.6
billion U.S. dollars worth of high-quality wheat every year and
had tried every possible means to halt its large wheat imports but
failed to find a high quality strain that also gives high yield.
</P>
<P>
Fan expects No. 906 to be widely used in China soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
