<HEADLINE> Mainland, Taiwan to Cooperate in Mountain Disasters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Experts in mountain disasters
from China's mainland and Taiwan have agreed to cooperate in
research into mountain disasters and conservation of the
environment.
</P>
<P>
A letter of intent to this effect was agreed upon during a
symposium on cross-straits mountain disasters and environmental
conservation held here.
</P>
<P>
More than 170 experts from Taiwan and China's mainland probed
the possibility of jointly launching research programs on the
function of forests and vegetation cover in anti-flood work and
comparison of land erosion in Taiwan and southwestern China.
</P>
<P>
Experts also agreed to launch more academic exchanges across
the Taiwan Straits as well as more short-term research programs in
the field.  
</P>
