BONN -- Germany's Social Democratic Party (SPD) announced
Monday to begin negotiations with the ecologist Greens on forming
a centre-left ruling coalition in Bonn after a landmark victory in
the general election a day earlier.
</P>
<P>
Gerhard Schroeder, who will be Germany's next chancellor after
the election triumph over the veteran chancellor Helmut Kohl, said
at a news conference in Bonn on Monday that the coalition talks
with the Greens will begin on Friday. (Germany-Coalition)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
