<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Drafts Document for Information Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Special
Economic Zone, the first of the five in China, has drafted a
document on improving information service.
</P>
<P>
The draft, "Regulations on the Development of Information
Industry in Shenzhen," also calls for overall planning and unified
standards in developing the information industry.
</P>
<P>
The regulations also stipulate that a memorandum should be
generated for each information development plan, and information
consulting service units should obtain licenses before starting a
business.
</P>
<P>
The document is believed to set a precedent for China's
information industry, according to sources.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen's neighbor Hong Kong is a leader in the information
industry, with an output value reaching 58.8 billion yuan (7.084
billion U.S. dollars) in 1997, 46.8 percent of the city's total
industrial output value.  
</P>
</TEXT>
