<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists Raise Potatoes Without Soil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have
developed techniques to raise potatoes without soil to improve
production and quality greatly.
</P>
<P>
Scientists at the Agriculture Academy of Sciences in
Heilongjiang Province, northeast China, developed the technique to
protect potatoes from contagious diseases that reduce production
sharply.
</P>
<P>
After cultivating potato buds in tubes, they put them in rock
and sawdust, and water them with nutrients. They later had
progress in putting the buds in a greenhouse where the buds grow
rapidly in the sealed environment, with weights that are five
times that of potatoes cultivated with the common technique.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
