<BODY>
<HEADLINE> West Ham Beats Southampton in English Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 28 (Xinhua) -- One goal from England
international striker Ian Wright helped West Ham United beat
bottom club Southampton 1-0 at the English Premier League on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
A diving header from the former Arsenal striker in the 61st
minute helped the London club climb from 11th to fourth where
they are level on points with Derby County and Wimbledon who in
second and third places respectively.
</P>
<P>
All three clubs, who have 12 points from seven games, are five
points behind league leaders Aston Villa.
</P>
<P>
Southampton put on the pressure in the second half and were
unlucky not to get a point. But they now have just one point from
their opening seven games. 
</P>
