<HEADLINE> Arafat Makes First Speech at General Debate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Palestinian leader made the speech for the first time since
the 52nd session of the General Assembly on July 7 voted
overwhelmingly to upgrade Palestine's status at the United
Nations, granting Palestine rights closer to those of a member
state, but not the right to vote.
</P>
<P>
"This participation is a manifestation of the resolution
adopted by your esteemed Assembly on the upgrading of Palestine's
presentation at the United Nations, which we consider to be an
essential step towards full membership," Arafat said.
</P>
<P>
By the resolution, the Palestine's mission is allowed to
participate in debates in the General Assembly, has the right of
reply in debates and the right to co-sponsor a resolution. It can
also raise points of order on proceedings related to Palestinian
and Middle East issues.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
